HEADWORD: Pharmaceutical
<hw>Phar`ma*ceu"tic*al</hw>
<pr>(-t⟦icr⟧*k⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pharmaceuticus</ets>, Gr. <grk>farmakeytiko`s</grk>, fr.
<grk>farmakey`ein</grk>: cf. F. <ets>pharmaceutique</ets>. See
<er>Pharmacy</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to the knowledge or art
of pharmacy, or to the art of preparing medicines according to the rules
or formulas of pharmacy; <as>as, <ex>pharmaceutical</ex>
preparations</as>.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Phar`ma*ceu"tic*al*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pharmaceutical chemistry</b></col>, <cd>that department
of chemistry which ascertains or regulates the composition of medicinal
substances.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pharmaceutics</ent>⟦br⟧
